# Game Client

## Stack

- Vanilla JS ES modules; no bundler unless explicitly added
- Canvas 2D for rendering; Socket.IO client from `/socket.io/socket.io.esm.min.js`
- Shared code imported from `/shared/` (constants, pathfinding, events)

## Structure

See [architecture.mdc](architecture.mdc). Canonical layout:

```
public/js/
├── main.js               # re-exports app/bootstrap.js
├── app/                  # PluginHost, UIManager, bootstrap
├── core/                 # GameLoop, InputRouter, Camera, PathFollower, FogOfWar
├── game/Game.js          # composition root — keep small
├── plugins/<feature>/    # registerClient, panels, input plugins
├── audio/                # AudioManager, GameAudio, MusicPlayer
├── render/               # renderers + layer registry (createDefaultLayers.js)
├── render/layers/        # HudLayer, MinimapLayer, …
├── debug/                # clientEventLog (server enables via DEBUG_EVENTS)
├── components/           # Panel, ItemRow
├── network/              # SocketClient
└── ui/                   # HUD widgets consumed by layers
```

## Plugin pattern

- Register client plugins in `public/js/app/loadClientPlugins.js`
- `PluginHost` wires socket events, panels, and game lifecycle
- Feature UI belongs in `public/js/plugins/<feature>/` — shared widgets in `ui/` (inventory, settings, chat)
- Modal panels that block input: toggle visibility in `Game.js`, handle in `InputRouter` / `CoreInput.js`
- Settings and audio prefs persist via `AudioManager` + `shared/audioSettings.js` (localStorage)

## Render layers

- `Renderer.js` owns an ordered layer list from `createDefaultLayers.js`
- New draw passes → new file in `render/layers/` + register with `order`
- Do not add ad-hoc draw calls in `Game.js` — extend the layer registry

## Client responsibilities

- **Render** world state; **interpolate** local player display position for smoothness
- **Merge deltas** — `GameLoop.setWorldState` applies `applyWorldStateDelta`; full entity arrays on map change
- **Never trust** client for gameplay outcomes — send intent, server decides
- Input → `InputRouter` / input plugins → socket events; world updates → render pipeline + `GameAudio` / `GameParticles`
- Screen ↔ world coords via `Camera.screenToWorld` / `worldToScreen`
- Zone travel: show `#map-loading-overlay` with name from `getMapDisplayName()` until map tiles arrive

## Performance

- Cull off-screen tiles and entities
- Throttle network sends (movement ~20 Hz), not every animation frame
- Reuse module instances; avoid allocations in the rAF loop where possible
